OL,3,CCross-party inquiry to explore suicide
OL,4,Cprevention measures
OL,6,FThe Inquiry will gather written and
OL,7,Foral evidence from charities,
OL,8,Fcommunity organisations, academics,
OL,9,Fstatutory partners and people working
OL,10,Fon the frontline. Organisations will
OL,11,Falso be invited to host site visits
OL,12,Fand evidence sessions so that MLAs can
OL,13,Fsee prevention work directly in
OL,14,Fcommunities.
OL,16,FThe work builds on growing evidence
OL,17,Fthat suicide prevention must address
OL,18,Fwider social and economic pressures
OL,19,Frather than relying solely on crisis
OL,20,Fintervention.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/9
